AGI -&nbsp;The research between the rubble of the ruins of the building collapsed last night around 19 a&nbsp;Bari, at the corner of Via Pinto and Via De Amicis continue without a stop. Around 1:00 this morning, one of the molecular dogs employed had barked and began to quickly dig at a point, which for the firefighters was the one where the 72-year-old woman, suffering from disability, was in her apartment, on the fourth floor, at the time of the collapse, as reported by her daughter.
The building had been cleared in February a year ago because it was perilous, but inside there were still the elderly and two families on the first floor, one absent at the time of the tragedy, the other managed to escape to the first scricchiolii. For hours teams of firefighters dig under the rubble to find the woman. Hours of apprehension for the daughter who followed the operations, between the tears, wrapped in a red duvet and the hood to shelter from the stinging cold. From research, still no results. Meanwhile, investigations on the collapse went to the Mobile Team of the Questura di&nbsp;Bari.&nbsp;
The Municipality of Bari has cancelled today the institutional activities organized by the administration. &nbsp;

